Aptman is a simple wrapper (visual hack) for Debian's Advanced Packaging Tool 
featuring visually attractive output and an interactive mode, inspired by the 
Pacman package manager and Yaourt front-end from the Arch Linux distribution.

Features:
  * Easy package searching with interactive search mode (inspired by yaourt)
  * Simple installing and removing programs, as well as system upgrade
  * Clean and colorful output
  * (Somewhat) configurable with config file ~/.aptman/prefs.py

Installation:
  * Download and extract the aptman script
  * chmod +x aptman and put it in your preferred bin directory

Visit the wiki for details: http://wiki.github.com/seanyeh/aptman/

Enjoy!
